EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Security Audit
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of database audit event classes.

EVENT.NAME: Audit Login
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Collects all new connection events since the trace was started, such as when a client requests a connection to a server running an instance of SQL Server.

EVENT.NAME: Audit Logout
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Collects all new disconnect events since the trace was started, such as when a client issues a disconnect command.

EVENT.NAME: Audit Server Starts And Stops
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Records service shut down, start, and pause activities.

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Progress Reports
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of events for progress reporting.

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Errors and Warnings
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of events for server errors.

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Discover Server State Events
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of events for server state discovers.

EVENT.NAME: Server State Discover Data
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Contents of the Server State Discover Response.

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Discover Events
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of events for discover requests.

EVENT.NAME: Lock Acquired
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: The locks were acquired by the transaction

EVENT.NAME: Lock Released
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: The locks were released by the transaction

EVENT.NAME: Lock Waiting
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: The locks are held by another transaction and therefore this transaction is blocking until the locks are released

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: Query Processing
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of key events during the process of a query execution.

EVENT.NAME: Query Subcube
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Query subcube, for Usage Based Optimization.

EVENT.NAME: Query Subcube Verbose
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Query subcube with detailed information. This event may have a negative impact on performance when turned on.

EVENT.NAME: Get Data From Aggregation
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Answer query by getting data from aggregation. This event may have a negative impact on performance when turned on.

EVENT.NAME: Get Data From Cache
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Answer query by getting data from one of the caches. This event may have a negative impact on performance when turned on.

EVENTCOLUMNSUBCLASS.NAME: Get data from measure group cache

EVENT.NAME: Resource Usage
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Reports reads, writes, cpu usage after end of commands and queries.

EVENT.NAME: Calculation Evaluation
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Information about the evaluation of calculations. This event will have a negative impact on performance when turned on.

EVENT.NAME: Calculation Evaluation Detailed Information
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: Detailed information about the evaluation of calculations. This event will have a negative impact on performance when turned on.

EVENT.NAME: DAX Query Plan
EVENT.DESCRIPTION: DAX logical/physical plan tree for VertiPaq and DirectQuery modes.

EVENTCATEGORY.NAME: File Load and Save
EVENTCATEGORY.DESCRIPTION: Collection of events for file load and save operations reporting.

COLUMN.NAME: EventClass
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Event Class is used to categorize events.

COLUMN.NAME: EventSubclass
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Event Subclass provides additional information about each event class.

COLUMN.NAME: CurrentTime
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Time at which the event started, when available. For filtering, expected formats are 'YYYY-MM-DD' and 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'.

COLUMN.NAME: StartTime
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Time at which the event started, when available. For filtering, expected formats are 'YYYY-MM-DD' and 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'.

COLUMN.NAME: EndTime
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Time at which the event ended. This column is not populated for starting event classes, such as SQL:BatchStarting or SP:Starting. For filtering, expected formats are 'YYYY-MM-DD' and 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'.

COLUMN.NAME: Duration
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Amount of time (in milliseconds) taken by the event.

COLUMN.NAME: CPUTime
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Amount of CPU time (in milliseconds) used by the event.

COLUMN.NAME: JobID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Job ID for progress.

COLUMN.NAME: SessionType
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Session type (what entity caused the operation).

COLUMN.NAME: ProgressTotal
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Progress total.

COLUMN.NAME: IntegerData
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Integer data.

COLUMN.NAME: ObjectID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Object ID (note this is a string).

COLUMN.NAME: ObjectType
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Object type.

COLUMN.NAME: ObjectName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Object name.

COLUMN.NAME: ObjectPath
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Object path. A comma-separated list of parents, starting with the object's parent.

COLUMN.NAME: ObjectReference
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Object reference. Encoded as XML for all parents, using tags to describe the object.

COLUMN.NAME: Severity
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Severity level of an exception.

COLUMN.NAME: Success
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: 1 = success. 0 = failure (for example, a 1 means success of a permissions check and a 0 means a failure of that check).

COLUMN.NAME: Error
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Error number of a given event.

COLUMN.NAME: ConnectionID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Unique connection ID.

COLUMN.NAME: DatabaseName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Name of the database in which the statement of the user is running.

COLUMN.NAME: NTUserName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Windows user name.

COLUMN.NAME: NTDomainName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Windows domain to which the user belongs.

COLUMN.NAME: ClientHostName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Name of the computer on which the client is running. This data column is populated if the host name is provided by the client.

COLUMN.NAME: ClientProcessID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The process ID of the client application.

COLUMN.NAME: ApplicationName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Name of the client application that created the connection to the server. This column is populated with the values passed by the application rather than the displayed name of the program.

COLUMN.NAME: SessionID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Session GUID.

COLUMN.NAME: NTCanonicalUserName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: User name in canonical form. For example, engineering.microsoft.com/software/someone.

COLUMN.NAME: SPID
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Server process ID. This uniquely identifies a user session. This directly corresponds to the session GUID used by XML/A.

COLUMN.NAME: TextData
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Text data associated with the event.

COLUMN.NAME: ServerName
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Name of the server producing the event.

COLUMN.NAME: RequestParameters
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Parameters for parameterized queries and commands.

COLUMN.NAME: RequestProperties
COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: XMLA request properties.
